Vessels Called In as Storm Nears, China News Says

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-07-28T14:27:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/vessels-called-in-as-storm-nears-china-news-says-correct-.html
(Corrects name of  news agency  in headline.)  Vessels and marine workers at sea
off Zhanjiang in southern  China ’s Guangdong province were asked
to return to land as Storm Nock-Ten approaches, China News
Service reported today, citing the local government.  The storm was 630 kilometers southeast of Zhanjiang at 4
p.m. local time today, with winds of as fast as 25 meters per
second, CNS said. Nock-Ten may make landfall between Guangdong
and Hainan provinces as soon as tomorrow night, it said, citing
China’s weather agency.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  